                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d534">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">723.2515/3254: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Peru</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Moore</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lima</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-01-22T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >January 22, 1929—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 7:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>8. My 6, January 20, 11 a.m. The engineers will not return to Lima until February
                    6. Their preliminary report will probably be ready for presentation by February
                    9.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Moore</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
